<!-- "SABAR" is a brand name of a private limited company, situated in Mumbai-India, who are manufacturing wide range of Health & Personal care and Ortho Rehabilitation Aid Products. -->
[[Image:M'bung M'bung's.jpg|200px|right|thumb|Two Sabar drums from Senegal]]
The '''sabar''', which originated with the [[Serer people]],<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=iLuy_dKKRKMC&pg=PA46&lpg=PA46&dq=sabar+drum+comes+from+serer&source=bl&ots=p1RhvZsy3P&sig=-IP4dh9-Nr1gvvx7qmlg_N2YnA0&hl=en&ei=4eAxTtz9IsGw8QPGx62hDg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9&ved=0CE4Q6AEwCA#v=onepage&q&f=false Master of Sabar] From the Sine-Saloum (two Serer precolonial kingdoms: [[Kingdom of Sine]] and [[Kingdom of Saloum]]. It originated from Sine and entered Saloum. Wolof migrants to Serer Saloum picked it up from their. See [[Mbalax]].</ref> is a traditional [[drum]] from [[Senegal]] (also played in [[the Gambia]]).  It is generally played with one hand and one stick.  Among its most renowned exponents was the Senegalese musician [[Doudou N'Diaye Rose]]. The sabar was used to communicate with other villages. The different rhythms correspond to phrases and could be heard for over 15 kilometers.

Sabar is also recognized as the style of music played while using this drum.

