{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Turks in Sweden | image = | caption = | population = {{Plainlist| * 100,000 Turkish citizens<ref>http://www.statistikdatabasen.scb.se/pxweb/en/ssd/START__BE__BE0101__BE0101E/UtrikesFoddaR/table/tableViewLayout1/?rxid=2b341905-7e62-4ea0-ae41-ccd602b6bed6</ref> * 100,000<ref>{{cite web|author=Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency|title=Turkiet är en viktig bro mellan Öst och Väst|url=http://www.sida.se/Svenska/Lander--regioner/Europa/Turkiet/Utvecklingen-i-Turkiet/|accessdate=2011-04-14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120911145333/http://www.sida.se/Svenska/Lander--regioner/Europa/Turkiet/Utvecklingen-i-Turkiet/|archivedate=2012-09-11|df=}}</ref><ref name=SwedishAffairs>{{cite web|author=Swedish Ministry for Foreign Affairs|title=Ankara Historia|url=http://www.swedenabroad.com/Page____24644.aspx|accessdate=2011-04-14|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722061226/http://www.swedenabroad.com/Page____24644.aspx|archivedate=2011-07-22|df=}}</ref>–150,000<ref name=sundayszaman>{{cite web|title=Swedish trade minister Ewa Björling calls on Turkey to cooperate in third countries |url=http://www.sundayszaman.com/sunday/newsDetail_getNewsById.action?newsId=241092|first=Ergin|last=Hava|work=Sundays Zaman|date=15 April 2011|accessdate=15 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Hurriyet Daily News|title=Businessman invites Swedes for cheap labor, regional access |url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/n.php?n=businessman-invites-swedish-for-cheap-labor-regional-access-2011-04-14|accessdate=2011-04-14}}</ref> or 200,000<ref>http://www.haberler.com/gurbetciler-isvec-te-turk-bankasi-istiyor-3894284-haberi/</ref> * Plus a further 30,000 [[Turks in Bulgaria|Bulgarian Turks]] and [[Macedonian Turks]]<ref>{{Harvnb|Laczko|Stacher|Klekowski von Koppenfels|2002|loc=187}}.</ref> }} | poptime = | popplace = {{Flatlist| * [[Stockholm]] ([[Rinkeby]], [[Tensta]], [[Alby, Botkyrka|Alby]]) * [[Gothenburg]] ([[Biskopsgården]], [[Hisingen]]) * [[Malmö]] ([[Rosengård]]) }} | langs = {{Flatlist| * [[Turkish language|Turkish]] * [[Swedish language|Swedish]] }} | rels = [[Sunni Islam]] | related = }}
'''Turks in Sweden''' or '''Swedish Turks''' ({{lang-sv|Turkar i Sverige}}; {{lang-tr|{{italics correction|İsveç Türkleri}}}}) are people of [[Turkish people|Turkish]] ethnicity living in [[Sweden]], mostly of [[Macedonian Turks|Macedonian Turkish]] and [[Bulgarian Turks|Bulgarian Turkish]] descent and ancestry from the Balkan states of [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] and [[Bulgaria]] while another large remainder of the ([[Turkish people|Turkish]]) ethnic minority has immigrant ancestral roots in [[Turkey]] proper. According to the [[Swedish Minister for Foreign Affairs]], there are 100,000 people in Sweden with a Turkish background, and a further 10,000 Swedish-Turks live in [[Turkey]].<ref name=SwedishAffairs/>
Turkish interpreters in Sweden have encouraged asylum seekers from Turkey to become informants on behalf of Turkish authorities.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=96&artikel=6900351|title=Flyktingspionage kan leda till att personer råkar illa ut|last=Malmöhus|first=P4|date=2018-03-06|work=Sveriges Radio|access-date=2018-07-14|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=83&artikel=6661130|title=Turkiet kartlägger oppositionella i Sverige|last=Öhman|first=Daniel|date=2017-03-28|work=Sveriges Radio|access-date=2018-07-14|language=sv}}</ref> Interpreters have also threatened to send information on regime critics to Turkish authorities.<ref name=":0" />
